
"You're the one who took him away! And you'll just as soon let them take Kali away!"
"No." His voice settled to something so soft, a flutter of sheets against bare skin, a whisper of feathers across the lips. "And they will not take you either."
His trigger finger tightened. The chamber exploded. She screamed and fired in return.
He had trained her himself. He had taught her how to fire, how to aim, and she had been the only of their four children to willingly practice firing. She was good. Even under pressure, she was good.
I stared at Lio, crumpled at my feet, a bullet in his forehead, his eyes staring sightlessly up at me.
He was dead.





